stylometry: Decision theory is the analytical and systematic way to tackle a problem.  Good decision making is based on logic.  The components are the decisions available to the decision maker, the set of possible outcomes, the probabilities of the set of possible outcomes, and finally the value model that determines the monetary value of decision outcome combinations.  The payoff table is a table that shows all of the possible decision outcome combinations, and provides an "easy-on-the-eye" way to anaylize all of the options.  Having them writen out in a table, makes it easy and clear to compare the combinations and helps the business make the best decision. If the outcomes are positive, it is a clear gain, if the outcomes are negative, the company would be losing money.
